					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12027532#post-4762109</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12027532/scp-4223#post-4762109</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 29 Aug 2020 22:36:25 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Rory Walker</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>137355</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is one of those articles that feels like it should be a joke, but it's so well done that it doesn't matter.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;that&nbsp;said,&nbsp;there's&nbsp;a&nbsp;minor&nbsp;typo</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;O5-13's&nbsp;hidden&nbsp;text&nbsp;reads:</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <blockquote> <p>&quot;But the next time we <em>kick turn 2000 on</em> and restart society&quot;</p> </blockquote> <p>That's presumably meant to be &quot;kick start 2000&quot; or &quot;turn 2000 on&quot;.</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>Also, taking normal redactions and making them hidden text is a really neat idea, especially for a silly skip like this one. It adds depth and makes you wonder what other things are &quot;anomolous&quot; that were once considered normal. Maybe the Foundation is enforcing their own idea of Normalcy on the world.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12027532#post-4385242</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12027532/scp-4223#post-4385242</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 02 Oct 2019 17:53:26 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>stormbreath</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3075960</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The other problem with this line of thought is that any recipe that would normally produce something that tastes like Baja Blast makes battery acid in this alt-dimension. That's what 4223-B is. It's authentic Baja Blast or nothing. Nothing that could be branded as Baja can be made - only other Mountain Dew products.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
